See article in <a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83030272/1915-11-10/ed-1/seq-16/" rel="nofollow">The sun, November 10, 1915, Page 16</a>: &quot;LAFAYETTE, NEW FRENCH LINER, COMES INTO PORT&quot;

The ship was renamed Mexique 1928 (<a href="http://www.ellisisland.org/shipping/Formatship.asp?shipid=472" rel="nofollow">www.ellisisland.org/shipping/Formatship.asp?shipid=472</a>)
During the WWI, was converted into a hospital ship (1400 beds) and then transport of troops. 19.06.1940: The ship was arriving in Bordeaux to pick up French parliamentarians bound for North Africa after the armistice with German when she struck a magnetic mine. No casualties (<a href="http://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?2430" rel="nofollow">www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?2430</a>)
